  <thingsToDo><![CDATA[<ul>
<li>Cable cars</li>
<li>Walking and hiking</li>
<li>Lake boat trips</li>
<li>Botanical garden</li>
<li>Golf</li>
<li>Museums</li>
<li>Shopping</li>
<li>Culture</li>
<li>E-bike hire</li>
</ul>
<p>For those staying in Locarno hotels, there are lots of activities and excursions to keep you busy. Among its major attractions are a lovely lake promenade lined with flowers and palm trees, luxuriant sub-tropical parks and gardens, access to wonderful wild valleys such as Valle Verzasca and the Centovalli - famous for its dramatic rail routes - and the ambient 'Piazza Grande' famous for its frequent concerts and other events. Boat rides can be taken to the Islands of Brissago in Switzerland, or the Borromean Islands and <a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/lakes-mountains-holidays/resorts/hotels/item802/stresa/" title="Stresa">Stresa</a> in <a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/lakes-mountains-holidays/country/item16/italy/" title="Italy">Italy</a>. A <strong>free</strong> return trip up Cardada is included for guests on holidays in Ascona who stay 7 or more nights.</p>
<p><strong>In and around Locarno</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Madonna del Sasso church, with fantastic views over the town, lake and mountains</li>
<li>Botanical gardens of Brissago islands with wide selection of flora</li>
<li>Day trips on Lake Maggiore for the Borromean islands and their gardens with fantastic exotic and tropical plants</li>
<li>Basilica of San pietro e Paolo in Borgo old town with art museum</li>
<li>'Lido Locarno’ public lido with swimming pools and thermal pool</li>
<li>6 &amp; 9 hole golf courses, plus 18-hole course in nearby Ascona &amp; Losone</li>
<li>'Moon and Stars’ music festival (approx 9-19 Jul)</li>
<li>'JazzAscona’ music festival (approx 20-29 Jun)</li>
<li>Locarno film festival (approx 7-17 Aug)</li>
<li>Folk festival takes place throughout June</li>
<li>Ascona Polo Cup takes place in July</li>
</ul>
<p>Discount Travel Card included for all Inghams guests</p>
<p><strong>Save up to 50% with your half-price travel card on trips of your choice across the Swiss transport network. Included in the price of your holiday, and worth over £100!</strong></p>
<p>NB. Discount card is not valid on Lake Maggiore</p>
<p>Travel card sent to you before departure with your rail transfer tickets.</p>
<p>Exploring on the Swiss Transport Network</p>
<p>Switzerland's excellent public transport network of mountain railways, cable-cars, steam boats and buses makes it a pleasure to explore the sights, at your own pace.</p>
<p>Evening bus service available</p>
<p>Car hire available </p>
<p> </p>]]></thingsToDo>
